      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start. i like the idea of inherited trauma. to make it feel more visceral and \"real,\" i want to lean into the specific reputation of the area. like, when people talk about these neighborhoods in movies or how they're portrayed in news, there's often this sense of lawlessness or unpredictability. \n\ncould u give me some specific story ideas where the \"danger\" of the neighborhood is actually tied to something supernatural? maybe like the concept of the streets themselves being unpredictable or the people there having a different kind of \"energy\" that makes it feel more chaotic or menacing to an outsider? i want to capture that specific tension between the residents and the perception of the place being a \"no-go zone.\"",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
